  "designDecisions": [
    "WHAT: Custom Node.js HTTP server in server.ts wrapping Next.js with ws library for WebSockets. WHY: Next.js App Router has no native WebSocket support; rather than polling (high latency) or Server-Sent Events (unidirectional), a custom server.ts attaches a ws.Server to the same HTTP server so WS and HTTP share port 3000. UPGRADE PATH: Extract WS to a separate Fastify/Node service behind a load balancer; swap in-process emitter for Redis pub/sub via ioredis.",
    "WHAT: In-process EventEmitter (ws-server.ts) used as the board-room pub/sub bus. WHY: Redis is an external service (violates constraints). The EventEmitter lives in the same Node process and broadcasts to all connected ws clients in O(n subscribers). UPGRADE PATH: Replace EventEmitter with Redis pub/sub (ioredis); each server instance subscribes to 'board:{boardId}' channels so multi-instance deployments work.",
    "WHAT: All persistent data stored in module-level Maps in store.ts (users, workspaces, sessions, boards, columns, cards, comments, notifications, invites). WHY: Zero-setup, no migration files, runs with npm run dev. UPGRADE PATH: Swap store.ts for a Prisma client; the function signatures in store.ts become the Prisma query layer with identical interfaces.",
    "WHAT: Passwords stored as plaintext strings with a PRODUCTION_UPGRADE comment. WHY: No crypto dependencies allowed; bcrypt is a native module requiring compilation. The plaintext approach is explicitly flagged and isolated to store.ts. UPGRADE PATH: npm install bcryptjs (pure JS, no compilation) and replace password comparison with bcryptjs.compare().",
    "WHAT: Session tokens are random UUIDs stored in a Map<token, userId> in auth.ts; sent as an HttpOnly SameSite=Strict cookie named 'session'. WHY: JWTs require a signing secret (env var, violates zero-env-vars constraint) and stateless validation. Cookie+Map gives logout invalidation for free with no secrets. UPGRADE PATH: Replace Map with Redis SETEX for distributed session storage; keep cookie mechanism unchanged.",
    "WHAT: LexoRank string-based position implemented from scratch in lexorank.ts (midpoint string generation between two strings). WHY: Avoids integer reorder storms (updating every sibling's sortOrder on insert) and avoids installing lexorank npm packages. UPGRADE PATH: Replace with the 'lexorank' npm package for production-grade bucket balancing.",
    "WHAT: Board data returned as a single denormalized GET /api/boards/[boardId] payload (board + columns + cards). WHY: Eliminates waterfall fetches; the PRD explicitly requires ≤200ms p95 for 500 cards. With in-memory Maps a single pass assembles the payload in <5ms. UPGRADE PATH: Add a Redis cache layer with boardId as key, invalidated on any card/column mutation.",
    "WHAT: @mention parsing done server-side in the POST /api/cards/[cardId]/comments route by scanning body for @{uuid} tokens and cross-referencing workspace membership. WHY: Server is the authority on valid userIds; client-side parsing could be spoofed with arbitrary userIds. Notifications are created atomically in the same request handler.",
    "WHAT: Drag-and-drop implemented with the HTML5 Drag and Drop API (no react-beautiful-dnd, no dnd-kit) using onDragStart/onDragOver/onDrop handlers in BoardView.tsx. WHY: Zero external dependencies. UPGRADE PATH: Replace with @dnd-kit/core for accessibility, touch support, and animation.",
    "WHAT: Card detail opens as a client-side modal (state in BoardView.tsx) without a route change. WHY: PRD explicitly requires no route change for card detail; avoids Next.js parallel routes complexity. The card URL (boardId + cardId) is preserved in the query string (?cardId=) for notification deep links. UPGRADE PATH: Migrate to Next.js parallel routes + intercepting routes for proper URL addressability."
  ],
